HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 766
By Vital
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Terry Evans of
Chattanooga.
WHEREAS, we were greatly saddened to learn of the passing of Terry Evans; and
WHEREAS, a compassionate man of faith, Mr. Evans was an outstanding husband,
teacher, coach, and advisor who poured the best of himself into each community that he was a
part of; and
WHEREAS, during his forty-one-year tenure with the McCallie School in Chattanooga,
he coached football at multiple levels and taught middle school science; additionally, he was the
Belk Dorm head, the Day Camp director, and the Middle School Senate advisor; and
WHEREAS, in his work, Mr. Evans consistently displayed a profound humility and
servant's heart; he inspired and mentored countless McCallie boys to grow into men of faith and
character; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Evans modeled and shared his love of Christ to his students and co-
workers alike; additionally, he taught men's Sunday School at Charity Baptist Church for fifty
years, up until his very last Sunday at the church; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Evans cherished the early mornings at home when he spent hours
reading and studying his Bible as he prepared to faithfully teach God's word; and
WHEREAS, Terry Evans will be sadly mourned but fondly remembered by his wife of
sixty-one years, Marilyn Evans; brother, Jim (Mary Ann) Evans; daughter, Tammy (Jim) Barber;
son, Roc (Sarah) Evans; grandchildren, Hamilton (Shelby) Barber, Andrew (Cristina) Barber,
Katy Beth Barber, Blake Evans, Sloane Evans, and Blaize Evans; and great-granddaughters,
Charlotte Barber and Hosanna Barber; and
HJR0766
011121
- 1 -

WHEREAS, he was preceded in death by his parents, Mr. and Mrs. Newman Ralph
Evans; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Evans leaves behind an indelible legacy of integrity and probity in public
life, compassion and loyalty in private life, and diligence and dedication in all his chosen
endeavors; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should remember the bountiful life of this exceptional
public servant and human being; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor the memory of Terry Evans, reflecting fondly upon his
impeccable character and his stalwart commitment to living the examined life with courage and
conviction.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we extend our sympathy and offer our condolences
to the family of Mr. Evans.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
